| ***DUE JULY 1, 202******5****** - $******580****** fee per lot******** (Includes Community Club Committee Annual donation $100) Rules and regulations of the Water Co-Op Emergency Response Plan **Generator** for the pump shack in case the power goes out, to be purchased in 2024. Kyle Whitton Electrician quote for install. Drought Conditions – currently no water restrictions but watch county for more information Irrigation water will be turned on by the UID at their discretion, they will not give notice when it will come on, likely mid-May which can also be used in emergencies (pump for fire events) SNOW REMOVAL a) call county first (2-4 days) b) private removal $500+GST this is necessary to ensure our community is safe for water, power, fire and ambulance services. **SNOW REMOVAL FUND to be started ($1,500 reserve).** ***Auditor needed – ******Sarah Greer*** Goal of reserve fund which started in 2019 at $4,000 currently $20,798.75 to grow to **$30.000** as costs are increasing. COMMUNITY IMPROVEMENT Committee INCLUDES Garbage – paid via the social club committee donation – currently has someone local that takes the garbage; as required and as funds are available. Weeds in grass (vote to approve) Tree grants Discussion on whether to reintroduce fish back into our pond. Fuel and maintenance on the lawn tractor. Grading the road via the county Multi activity (volleyball, badminton, tetherball) poles will be installed this spring in the circular green space – looking for a net for these activities. Social activities over the summer?  Is the community interested in events like: BBQ/potluck Sports day Water meetup (visit on the pond with kayaks, canoe, paddleboard, etc.) Next meeting Q2 MVWB Meeting **Wednesday July 16, 2025 @ 7 PM** **Community Improvement meeting ****Wednesday June 4, 2025 @ 7PM****.** |